post_text:
Good Evening;

If we have your parent email address on file, you should have received an invite email from welsupport@waterford.org for Waterford (Grades K-2) this is an excellent resource that the students use in class.

For the full step-by-step setup guide, visit this link: https://www.brainshark.com/waterford/vu?pi=zHNzlx6PvzP2FXz0&intk=848114685

Please be advised;

This is a follow-up to the letter posted on the districts social media pages and sent home on Wednesday afternoon;

Clairton City School District will have a 11:30am early release on Thursday 09/19/19 and will be closed on Friday 9/20/19 for preparation and administration of a secondary treatment.

All after school activities will be cancelled on Thursday and Friday. The Home Football Game at Neil C. Brown will still take place and is scheduled for a 7pm kickoff.

As always our number one priority is the safety and well-being of our students and staff and we will continue to take all necessary precautions and safety measures. As always it is at the parents discretion to keep the student home (this would be an excused absence, if a note is received to the office within 3 days of returning)

School will resume on Monday 9/23/19.

